	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon2.gif" alt="Arrow" border="0"> <b>READ THIS BEFORE POSTING an application!</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><font color="yellow"><b>Thank you for your interest in The Mystical Order.</b></font><br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise"><b>Before you post an application, please follow these steps:</font></b><br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise">[1]</font> Start by reading --&gt; <a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=1693" target="_blank">Edarion's Recruiting Post</a> &lt;-- which is stickied at the top of this forum.  Read over it thoroughly and familiarize yourself with all of its content. <br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise">[2]</font> Check whether or not your class is currently being recruited, and if it is, determine if you meet the minimum requirements for applicants of your particular class.  <a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/forums/showthread.phps=&threadid=1693" target="_blank">Check Edarion's post</a> to find out which classes we are currently recruiting and the minimum requirements.  <br />
<br />
<u>Note</u>: Recruiting and requirements change frequently so be sure that you have checked these.  <b>As of 9-30-03, new AA and flag requirements are in place</b>.<br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise">[3a]</font> If we are recruiting your class and if you meet the minimum requirements for applicants of your class, start a new thread in this forum enclosing your application.  Be absolutely sure that your application contains all of the information <a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=1693" target="_blank">requested by Edarion.</a>  Write your application in a well-organized and easy to read format.  Incomplete applications will not be considered.<br />
<br />
<u>Note</u>: Edarion's reference to being of <a href="http://www.mysticalorder.org/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=1693" target="_blank">key classes</a> is important.  If recruiting for your class is currently closed, but you feel TMO should consider you anyway, you'll need to include the names of 10 TMO recommendations in your application.  Applications from closed classes that do not include those recommendations will not be considered.<br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise">[3b]</font> If you do <i>not</i> meet the minimum requirements to apply, do not post an application until you meet them.  Applicants which do not meet the requirements will not be considered, and the application will likely be closed.<br />
<br />
<font color="turquoise">[4]</font> When you have posted your application, contact <b>Exotika</b> or <b>Macery</b> as soon as possible in game or via the private messaging system on this message board.  A brief conversation will take place to discuss your application, to answer questions about the application process, to provide information regarding what to expect as an applicant, and after steps [1] through [3] have been properly completed, to invite you into our applicant guild.  You will also at that time be given instructions regarding joining our raid channels. <br />
<br />
<b><font color="red">Disclaimer: Edarion has the final say regarding invitations to our applicant guild.</font></b><br />
<br />
<i>Keep in mind that once invited into our applicant guild, you will be expected to uphold the standards of a TMO member.</i>  <br />
You will be expected to attend every raid that you are online for, and you will be expected to be online and contributing to the guild when you are not at work, at school, or otherwise committed.  Remember that the manner in which you carry yourself in game, and any actions that you choose to do, will reflect upon TMO, good and bad alike.<br />
<br />
<i>The most frequently asked question is, "How long will I be an app?"</i><br />
The keys to earning a TMO tag are high raid attendance and exellent raid performance.  Expect a minimum of 1 month of high attendance and exellent performance before being considered for a TMO tag, but your app time can range anywhere from a few weeks to a few months depending on the individual and is at the sole discretion of Edarion.<br />
<br />
<u>Note</u>: If you receive a lot of "No" votes, it will appear that your application is not being supported, and your application may be closed.<br />
<br />
<font color="yellow">Contact Exotika, Macery, or Gemdiver with any questions regarding the application process.</font></font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
